description:
&lt;p&gt;Various hours available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a registered nurse based at Integrated Central Hub, working within City and Penderi Clusters including a Residential Enablement Unit in Swansea, the district nursing service and the single point of access department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve supporting the caseload holders within the district nursing service and the Band 6 Nurse Assessor in the management of patients at the Residential Enablement Unit and the single point of access dept.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will require a high standard of clinical skills; undertaking procedures including wound care, diabetes management, palliative care, monitoring patients medication, venepuncture and male &amp; female catheterisation. These skills are also essential in the role of single point of access dept, who receive referrals and act accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vicky Lloyd Assistant District Nurse Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vicky.Lloyd@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
